Heatmaps based on contribution to phenotype

Each allele has an additive effect on the phenotype, which is stored in the vcf@fix[,"INFO"] as S. IF the mutation type is 2 (MT=2), the additive effect of an allele on that individuals phenotype is S*(the number of alleles).

For neutral mutations (MT=1) and inversion mutations (MT=3), S=0, so they wont affect the calculation.
